<paragraph blockId="42.[264,1323,284,990]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
Distribution. A riverine species captured at low elevations from September to August in 
<collectingCountry box="[294,374,764,790]" name="Kenya" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Kenya</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="42.[264,1323,284,990]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
Etymology. Latin, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Scarbrough &amp; Marascia" authorityYear="2003" box="[534,622,804,829]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Ommatius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="litoreus">
<emphasis box="[534,622,804,829]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">litoreus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, meaning shore or beach, referring to the site where specimens were collected.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="42.[264,1323,284,990]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
Remarks. In addition to the characters in the key, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Scarbrough &amp; Marascia" authorityYear="2003" box="[908,1034,884,909]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Ommatius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="litoreus">
<emphasis box="[908,1034,884,909]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">O. litoreus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is also distinguished by the presence of stout ventral bristles on the base of the fore femur (
<figureCitation box="[1066,1153,924,950]" captionStart="FIGURES 21­28" captionStartId="65.[264,382,1754,1778]" captionTargetBox="[277,1313,348,1567]" captionTargetId="figure-98@65.[242,1321,324,1693]" captionTargetPageId="65" captionText="FIGURES 21­28. Right wing of male Ommatius (Pygommatius) spp. 21. O. talus, sp. n.; 22. O. vultus, sp. n.; 23­28. Right fore femur of male Ommatius (Pygommatius) spp. showing arrangement of anteroventral bristles. 23. O. brevicornis Curran; 24. O. grossus, sp. n.; 25. O. limbus, sp. n.; 26. O. litoreus, sp. n.; 27. O. strigiatus, sp. n..; 28. O. vultus, sp. n." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5019049" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5019049/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
) and the stout posteroventral bristles and numerous, short, comb­like bristles on the middle femur.
</paragraph>
